":"0580/21/O/N/23 Q06","year":2023,"session":"OctNov","tex":"For each of 10 people working in an office, the scatter diagram shows their salary and the value of their car.\n\n\\begin{InsertScreenShot}\n\n\\end{InsertScreenShot}\n\n(a) One of these people has a salary of \\$28 000.\n\nFind the value of their car.\n\n(b) Another person starts to work in the office.\nTheir salary is \\$54 000 and the value of their car is \\$6100.\n\nPlot this information on the scatter diagram.\n\n(c) What type of correlation is shown in the scatter diagram?","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":1},{"label":"(c)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"draw"},{"id":"0580-2023OctNov-Paper21-Q07","paper":"2023OctNov-Paper21","qnum":7,"marks":1,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.16","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Money","qtype":"money and currency","g":"mixed","src":"0580/21/O/N/23 Q07","year":2023,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The exchange rate between Singapore dollars and euros is 1 Singapore dollar = 0.62 euros.\n\nFind the value of 161.20 euros in Singapore dollars.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find","answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"Singapore dollars"}},{"id":"0580-2023OctNov-Paper21-Q08","paper":"2023OctNov-Paper21","qnum":8,"marks":1,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/21/O/N/23 Q08","year":2023,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Calculate.\n\\[\n7\\frac{3}{11} \\times 3\\frac{3}{10}\n\\]","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2023OctNov-Paper21-Q09","paper":"2023OctNov-Paper21","qnum":9,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.1","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Types of number","qtype":"types of number","g":"mixed","src":"0580/21/O/N/23 Q09","year":2023,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Find the highest common factor (HCF) of 140 and 126.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-